                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12906817" author="ssc" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 15:30:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I did not like the idea to load a file containing all user/item pairs to filter into memory in the final Reducer which was proposed on the mailing list, as this might introduce scaling issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think I found a better way to include the filtering logic in the distributed recommendation process. For a user that should not be recommended an item we join an artificial NaN summand into the estimation of his/her preference towards that item so that this item will automatically be excluded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch is coming soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906822" author="ssc" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 15:38:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch provided for review.  I plan to commit this tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
